cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.MM

The paper discusses the development of deep quaternion networks for classification and segmentation tasks, which falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), neural networks (cs.NE), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper uses the CIFAR-10 and CIFAR-100 datasets, which are commonly used in the computer vision community, and the KITTI Road Segmentation dataset, which is used for segmentation tasks in computer vision. Therefore, cs.MM (multimedia) is also a possible category.
